A federal judge allowed Tyco International Ltd. shareholders to proceed with a class action lawsuit.
The lawsuit involves allegations of fraud and corporate looting by former directors and officers.
Former executives, Kozlowski and Swartz, are accused of stealing over $600 million from Tyco.
Prosecutors claim they pocketed millions more by lying about the company's finances.
The retrial focuses on illegal acts like erasing huge loans from the books.
Kozlowski denies involvement in lavish spending accusations.
The trial highlights corporate scandals impacting workers, clients, and stockholders.
Prosecutors emphasize the men's deception and concealment of payments.
